{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/PagerView"],"generated":true}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IndicatorView"}],"title":"IndicatorView","roleHeading":"Structure","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"struct","externalID":"s:12SwiftUIPager13IndicatorViewV","modules":[{"name":"SwiftUIPager"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"IndicatorView"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Indicator that shows a horizontal collection of dots."}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/IndicatorView","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/IndicatorView\/init(count:index:style:)"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/IndicatorView\/body"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/IndicatorView\/View-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftuipager\/indicatorview"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IndicatorView"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The IndicatorView takes a binding that reflects the currently active dot. Modifing this binding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will automatically select the respective dot inside the indicator. Likewise the binding is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"adjusted when the indicator is used to change the selected dot. The selection can be changed by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simple tap gestures to the desired dot or by scrubbing the collection with a drag gesture."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The IndicatorView adjusts its size to the amount of dots. If the indicator cannot fit all dots,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the collection starts scrolling when scrubbing past the edges of the Indicator."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The IndicatorView is independent from any Pager, it can be used for any kind of page"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"representation through it’s index binding. However, if used with the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/PagerView"},{"type":"text","text":" that comes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with this library, there are dedicated view modifiers, that provide convienient access to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"customize the PageIndicator."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple encourages to think twice when deciding which UI Element to use in its Human"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Interface Guidelines. In this context an Indicator like this might not be the best tool when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indicating the current selection of an element in a collection with many elements (which would"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"required too much scrolling)."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"